---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Gesture Volume Controller | Sam Popham" noParticles>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
      Gesture Volume Controller — Deep Dive
    </h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      Background computer vision system using MediaPipe to map stable hand poses
      to system volume with a calibration tray.
    </p>

    <!-- Hero image -->
    <figure class="mb-12">
      <!--
        Image guidance:
        Complete gesture controller demo:
        - hand in view with landmark overlay, calibration controls, and volume feedback visible,
        - showcase the full workflow in one comprehensive screenshot or GIF.
      -->
      <img
        src="/src/assets/images/deep-dives/gesture/up-down-use.gif"
        alt="Gesture volume controller in action"
        class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      />
    </figure>

    <!-- Key features in text-only sections -->
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">
          Landmark Overlay & Confidence
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Which keypoints matter and why — visualising confidence lets you trust
          the system's decisions. Clear hand silhouette with numbered keypoints
          and confidence circles show you exactly which joints the system is
          tracking.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Calibration & Tray UI</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Adjust sensitivity and map gestures quickly — fine-tuning should be
          easy and fast. A compact tray window lets you adjust sliders and test
          gesture mappings without cluttering the main screen.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Live Feedback HUD</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Immediate visual feedback helps users understand mapping and avoid
          accidental volume jumps. A small overlay shows live mapped volume
          level as gestures are performed, with clear numeric and graphical
          feedback.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
>
